# Backend Code Review Report

## Summary
| Severity | Count |
|---|---|
| 🔴 Critical (broken data flow) | 2 |
| 🟠 High (duplication/dead code) | 5 |
| 🟡 Medium (inconsistency/cleanup) | 4 |

---

## 🔴 Critical Issues

### 1. Student fee page reads from wrong collection
**Files:** [api/student/fees/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/student/fees/route.ts) ↔ `api/admin/students/[id]/fees/route.ts`

**Problem:** Admin creates/updates fees using [StudentFee](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentFee.ts#11-31) model. But `GET /api/student/fees` reads from [FeeRecord](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/%28admin%29/admin/students/page.tsx#28-37) (a different collection entirely). Students can **never** see their fees.

```
Admin writes → StudentFee collection
Student reads → FeeRecord collection ← completely different!
```

**Fix:** Change [api/student/fees/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/student/fees/route.ts) to read from [StudentFee](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentFee.ts#11-31) instead of [FeeRecord](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/%28admin%29/admin/students/page.tsx#28-37).

---

### 2. POST /api/admin/students/[id]/fees still reads CoursePricing
**File:** `api/admin/students/[id]/fees/route.ts` line 81

**Problem:** The POST handler auto-fills `baseFee` by querying the old [CoursePricing](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/CoursePricing.ts#3-15) collection instead of `Program.pricing`. This is the old broken data source we migrated away from.

```ts
// Line 81 — WRONG
const pricing = await CoursePricing.findOne({ courseId });
// Should be:
const program = await Program.findOne({ code: courseId });
const baseFee = program.pricing.totalFee;
```

**Fix:** Replace [CoursePricing](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/CoursePricing.ts#3-15) lookup with `Program.findOne({ code: courseId })` then read `program.pricing`.

---

## 🟠 High Issues

### 3. Three parallel fee models doing the same thing
**Models:** [StudentFee.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentFee.ts), [FeeRecord.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/FeeRecord.ts), `FeePayment.ts + FeeStructure.ts`

| Model | Used by | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| [StudentFee](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentFee.ts#11-31) | admin/fees panel, student profile | Active fee tracking per student |
| [FeeRecord](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/%28admin%29/admin/students/page.tsx#28-37) | `admin/finance/fee-records` API | Duplicate fee tracking (old ERP) |
| [FeePayment](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/FeePayment.ts#13-33) + [FeeStructure](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/FeeStructure.ts#3-14) | `admin/finance/payments` API | Another parallel system (academic ERP style) |

**Problem:** All three do fee management. Only [StudentFee](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentFee.ts#11-31) is actively used in the main admin fee panel. The other two create confusion and dead DB collections.

**Fix:** Keep [StudentFee](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentFee.ts#11-31) as the sole source. Deprecate [FeeRecord](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/%28admin%29/admin/students/page.tsx#28-37), [FeeStructure](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/FeeStructure.ts#3-14), [FeePayment](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/FeePayment.ts#13-33)— remove their API routes or clearly label them as unused until fully deleted.

---

### 4. Two parallel Library models for different features
**Models:** [Library.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Library.ts) (simple), [LibraryDocument.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/LibraryDocument.ts) (advanced)

| Model | Used by |
|---|---|
| [Library](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Library.ts#3-15) | `api/public/library`, old admin library upload |
| [LibraryDocument](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/LibraryDocument.ts#3-18) | `api/admin/library/documents`, new versioned library |

**Problem:** Two library systems coexist. The public library page reads from [Library](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Library.ts#3-15) (old). The new admin uploads are in [LibraryDocument](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/LibraryDocument.ts#3-18) with versioning, categories etc. Public page never shows the newer richer content.

**Fix:** Public library API should read from [LibraryDocument](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/LibraryDocument.ts#3-18). Migrate any old [Library](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Library.ts#3-15) records. Delete [Library.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Library.ts).

---

### 5. Two document submission systems
**Models:** [StudentDocuments.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentDocuments.ts) (admission docs), [DocumentSubmission.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/DocumentSubmission.ts) (DMS V2)

| Model | Used by | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| [StudentDocuments](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentDocuments.ts#17-43) | `api/admin/students/[id]/documents`, registration flow | Admission documents (photo, marksheets, Aadhaar) |
| `DocumentSubmission` | `api/admin/documents/submissions`, `api/teacher/documents` | Ongoing document requirements system |

**Note:** These serve different purposes — admission docs vs ongoing requirements — so both are needed. But the [StudentDocuments](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentDocuments.ts#17-43) model has a **legacy `aadhaarIdUrl` field** kept alongside the newer `aadhaarFrontUrl + aadhaarBackUrl` split fields. This creates ambiguity in validation code.

**Fix:** Remove `aadhaarIdUrl` / `aadhaarIdType` from [StudentDocuments](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentDocuments.ts#17-43) schema (or mark deprecated). Update any reads to check new fields only.

---

### 6. CoursePricing model is now orphaned but still imported
**File:** `api/admin/students/[id]/fees/route.ts` line 7

**Problem:** [CoursePricing](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/CoursePricing.ts#3-15) model is still imported and used in one POST handler (Issue #2 above). The model itself still exists in [/models/CoursePricing.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/CoursePricing.ts) even though we migrated to `Program.pricing`.

**Fix:** After fixing Issue #2, the model becomes unused. Delete [CoursePricing.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/CoursePricing.ts) and its import.

---

### 7. [/api/admin/course-pricing/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/course-pricing/route.ts) is now a dead API
**File:** [api/admin/course-pricing/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/course-pricing/route.ts)

**Problem:** This API was originally paired with the [admin/course-pricing/page.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/admin/course-pricing/page.tsx) which was deleted. The API has been rewritten to use Program model — but no UI calls it anymore. Fee management is now fully in `admin/courses` (via `Program.pricing`).

**Fix:** Delete [api/admin/course-pricing/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/course-pricing/route.ts).

